cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image deblurring, which is a computer vision task, so it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for deblurring, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions large-scale datasets, which could indicate that it belongs to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new network structure, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
